## Phase 1.5 ‚Äî KYC & Identity Verification ‚¨ÖÔ∏è NEW
**Goal**: Tiered KYC verification with document upload, face matching, AML screening, and automated tier upgrades.

| Step | Domain | Task | Details |
|------|--------|------|---------|
| 1.5.1 | Entity | **KycDocument entity** | `id (UUID)`, `userId`, `documentType` (NRC_FRONT/NRC_BACK/PASSPORT/SELFIE/PROOF_OF_ADDRESS), `verificationStatus` (NOT_SUBMITTED/PENDING/APPROVED/REJECTED), `fileUrl` (encrypted S3 path), `fileHash` (SHA-256), `rejectionReason`, `providerReference`, `providerResponse` (JSON), `verifiedAt`, `expiresAt`, `createdAt`, `updatedAt` |
| 1.5.2 | Entity | **KycTier entity** | `id (UUID)`, `userId`, `currentTier` (NONE/TIER_1/TIER_2/TIER_3), `maxBalance` (BigDecimal), `dailyTransferLimit`, `dailyDepositLimit`, `lastTierUpgradeAt`, `upgradedBy` (nullable admin UUID), `createdAt`, `updatedAt` |
| 1.5.3 | Entity | **KycTier enum** | `NONE`, `TIER_1`, `TIER_2`, `TIER_3` |
| 1.5.4 | Migration | **Flyway V11, V12** | `V11__create_kyc_documents_table.sql`, `V12__create_kyc_tiers_table.sql` |
| 1.5.5 | Service | **KycService** | `submitDocument(userId, documentType, file)` ‚Äî validate file type/size, encrypt file, upload to S3, create KycDocument (PENDING), call KYC provider for verification; `getKycStatus(userId)` ‚Äî return current tier + document statuses; `upgradeTier(userId, newTier)` ‚Äî called on verification success, enforces one-directional upgrade |
| 1.5.6 | Service | **KycProviderClient** | Interface for provider abstraction: `verifyIdentity(userId, documents)` ‚Üí `VerificationResult`. Implementations: `SmileIdClient`, `DojahClient`, `IdentityPassClient`. Configurable via `application.yml` |
| 1.5.7 | Service | **KycLimitEnforcer** | `validateTransactionLimit(userId, amount, type)` ‚Äî checks current KYC tier against daily limits, throws `KycLimitExceededException` if exceeded. Called by TransactionService before processing. `validateBalanceCap(walletId, newBalance)` ‚Äî checks against KYC tier max balance cap |
| 1.5.8 | Controller | **KycController** | `POST /api/v1/kyc/documents` (upload, multipart), `GET /api/v1/kyc/status` (current tier + docs), `POST /api/v1/kyc/submit` (trigger verification for submitted docs) |
| 1.5.9 | Controller | **Admin KYC endpoints** | `GET /api/v1/admin/kyc/pending` (list pending docs), `POST /api/v1/admin/kyc/{docId}/approve`, `POST /api/v1/admin/kyc/{docId}/reject` (with reason), `POST /api/v1/admin/kyc/users/{userId}/downgrade` (compliance downgrade) |
| 1.5.10 | Integration | **File storage** | AWS S3 or MinIO (dev) for encrypted document storage. Generate pre-signed URLs for document viewing (time-limited). AES-256 server-side encryption |
| 1.5.11 | Integration | **AML screening** | On Tier 2+ upgrade, check user identity against sanctions/PEP lists via KYC provider or separate AML API |
| 1.5.12 | Integration | **KYC callback/webhook** | Provider sends async verification result ‚Üí `POST /api/v1/webhooks/kyc` ‚Üí update document status + tier upgrade if approved |
| 1.5.13 | DTO | **KYC DTOs** | `KycDocumentResponse`, `KycStatusResponse`, `KycSubmitResponse`, `KycDocumentUploadRequest` (multipart) |
| 1.5.14 | Security | **KYC limits wired into transactions** | Modify `TransactionService` deposit/withdraw/transfer to call `KycLimitEnforcer` before processing; modify wallet balance update to check `KycLimitEnforcer.validateBalanceCap` |
| 1.5.15 | Enhancement | **Selfie + NRC face match** | On Tier 2 submission, send selfie + NRC to provider for liveness check and face comparison. Provider returns match score (threshold: >80%) |
| 1.5.16 | Test | **KYC service tests** | Document upload, provider integration (mock), tier upgrade logic, limit enforcement |
| 1.5.17 | Test | **KYC limit enforcement tests** | Verify daily limit exceeded returns 403, balance cap enforced, tier upgrade one-directional |

**Deliverable**: Multi-tier KYC with document upload, provider verification, AML screening, face matching. Transaction limits enforced by KYC tier. Admin approval/rejection workflow.

### KYC Balance & Transaction Limits Matrix

| Tier | Max Balance | Daily Transfer Out | Daily Deposit In | Features |
|------|-------------|-------------------|------------------|----------|
| NONE | ZMW 0 | ZMW 0 | ZMW 0 | Read-only profile |
| TIER_1 | ZMW 5,000 | ZMW 1,000 | ZMW 2,500 | P2P transfers only |
| TIER_2 | ZMW 50,000 | ZMW 10,000 | ZMW 25,000 | Flutterwave, Virtual Cards |
| TIER_3 | ZMW 500,000+ | ZMW 100,000 | ZMW 250,000 | Full features, mass payouts |

