## Phase 4 ‚Äî Fee Engine & Audit Logging
**Goal**: Configurable fee calculation per transaction type. Audit log for all balance changes.

| Step | Domain | Task | Details |
|------|--------|------|---------|
| 4.1 | Entity | **FeeConfiguration entity** | `id`, `transactionType` (TRANSFER/WITHDRAWAL/DEPOSIT), `percentageFee` (BigDecimal), `flatFee` (BigDecimal), `minFee`, `maxFee`, `active` (boolean), `createdAt`, `updatedAt` |
| 4.2 | Migration | **Flyway V5, V6** | `V5__create_fee_configurations_table.sql`, `V6__create_audit_logs_table.sql` |
| 4.3 | Entity | **AuditLog entity** | `id (UUID)`, `entityType` (string), `entityId` (UUID), `action` (string), `oldValue` (text), `newValue` (text), `performedBy` (UUID), `ipAddress` (string), `createdAt` (timestamp) ‚Äî **append-only**, no update/delete operations |
| 4.4 | Service | **FeeEngineService** | `calculateFee(transactionType, amount)` ‚Äî loads active config, computes: `totalFee = (amount * percentageFee / 100) + flatFee`, clamped by min/max, rounded to 2 decimals HALF_EVEN |
| 4.5 | Service | **Fee deduction** | Modify transfer flow to deduct fee from sender's wallet and create FEE transaction record linked to transfer |
| 4.6 | Controller | **Fee estimation** | `GET /api/v1/fees/estimate?type=TRANSFER&amount=100.00` ‚Äî read-only, no auth required (or lightweight auth) |
| 4.7 | Service | **AuditService** | `recordAction(entityType, entityId, action, oldValue, newValue, performedBy, ipAddress)` ‚Äî `@Async` (non-blocking), returns `CompletableFuture<Void>` |
| 4.8 | AOP | **Audit annotation** | `@Audited(action="DEPOSIT")` ‚Äî optional AOP aspect that auto-captures method params for balance changes |
| 4.9 | Controller | **Admin fee config** | `GET/PUT /api/v1/admin/fees/{id}` ‚Äî ADMIN-only CRUD for fee configurations |
| 4.10 | Test | **FeeEngine tests** | Percentage + flat, rounding, min/max clamping, inactive config fallback |
| 4.11 | Test | **AuditService tests** | Verify async behavior, data capture |

**Deliverable**: Fees calculated and deducted on transfers. Audit log recording every balance change asynchronously.

---

## Phase 5 ‚Äî Refresh Token Rotation, Rate Limiting & Idempotency
**Goal**: Production-grade auth security, API protection, and duplicate charge prevention.

| Step | Domain | Task | Details |
|------|--------|------|---------|
| 5.1 | Service | **Refresh token rotation** | `refreshAccessToken(refreshToken)` ‚Äî hash incoming token, match DB, check expiry + not revoked, issue new access + new refresh, revoke old refresh; if token already revoked (stolen detection) ‚Üí revoke ALL tokens for user |
| 5.2 | Controller | **Refresh endpoint** | `POST /api/v1/auth/refresh` ‚Äî accepts `refreshToken` in body, returns new `AuthResponse` |
| 5.3 | Service | **Logout / revoke** | `POST /api/v1/auth/logout` ‚Äî revoke current refresh token; `POST /api/v1/auth/logout-all` ‚Äî revoke all user tokens |
| 5.4 | Entity | **IdempotencyKey entity** | `id`, `key` (unique), `responseBody` (text/JSON), `responseStatusCode` (int), `expiresAt` (createdAt + 24h) |
| 5.5 | Migration | **Flyway V7, V8** | `V7__create_idempotency_keys_table.sql`, `V8__idempotency_index.sql` |
| 5.6 | Filter | **IdempotencyFilter** | `OncePerRequestFilter` ‚Äî extract `Idempotency-Key` header for POST/PATCH to financial endpoints; if key exists ‚Üí return cached response; else proceed + cache after successful completion |
| 5.7 | Filter | **RateLimitingFilter** | Token-bucket algorithm per user (authenticated) or per IP (unauthenticated). Configurable limits. Default: 100 req/min per user, 10 req/min for auth endpoints |
| 5.8 | Headers | **Rate limit response headers** | `X-RateLimit-Limit`, `X-RateLimit-Remaining`, `X-RateLimit-Reset` on every response via `OncePerRequestFilter` |
| 5.9 | Error | **429 response** | `RateLimitExceededException` ‚Üí `Retry-After` header + standard error JSON |
| 5.10 | Test | **Refresh token rotation tests** | Happy path, expired token, stolen token detection (reuse), all-tokens-revoked scenario |
| 5.11 | Test | **Rate limiting tests** | Token bucket consumption, refill, header accuracy, 429 beyond limit |

**Deliverable**: Refresh token rotation with theft detection. API rate-limited per user/IP. Idempotent financial operations.

---

## Phase 6 ‚Äî Notifications, Scheduling & Caching
**Goal**: Async email/SMS alerts, scheduled cleanup jobs, and cache for hot data.

| Step | Domain | Task | Details |
|------|--------|------|---------|
| 6.1 | Entity | **Notification entity** | `id (UUID)`, `userId`, `type` (EMAIL/SMS), `channel`, `recipient`, `subject`, `body`, `status` (PENDING/SENT/FAILED), `retryCount`, `maxRetries` (3), `createdAt`, `sentAt` |
| 6.2 | Entity | **NotificationAttempt entity** | `id`, `notificationId`, `attemptNumber`, `status`, `errorMessage`, `attemptedAt` |
| 6.3 | Migration | **Flyway V9, V10** | `V9__create_notifications_table.sql`, `V10__create_notification_attempts_table.sql` |
| 6.4 | Service | **NotificationService** | `sendEmailNotification(to, subject, body)` ‚Äî `@Async`, creates Notification record, calls JavaMailSender, updates status on completion/failure. Retry up to 3 times on failure |
| 6.5 | Service | **SmsService** | `sendSms(phone, message)` ‚Äî `@Async`, creates Notification record, calls Africa's Talking API (HTTP), updates status |
| 6.6 | Integration | **Transaction notifications** | Hook into TransactionService after successful deposit/withdraw/transfer ‚Üí fire async email + SMS |
| 6.7 | Integration | **KYC notifications** | On KYC tier upgrade or document rejection, send email notification to user |
| 6.8 | Scheduler | **Pending transaction cleanup** | `@Scheduled(cron = "0 0 3 * * *")` ‚Äî mark PENDING transactions older than 24h as FAILED (idempotent) |
| 6.9 | Scheduler | **Idempotency key cleanup** | `@Scheduled(cron = "0 0 4 * * *")` ‚Äî delete idempotency records older than 24h (idempotent) |
| 6.10 | Scheduler | **Expired refresh token cleanup** | `@Scheduled(cron = "0 30 4 * * *")` ‚Äî delete/revoke expired refresh tokens (idempotent) |
| 6.11 | Scheduler | **Flutterwave transfer reconciliation** | `@Scheduled(fixedRate = 900000)` ‚Äî every 15 min poll pending Flutterwave transfers for status updates |
| 6.12 | Caching | **Cache configuration** | Spring Cache + Caffeine ‚Äî cache wallet balance (evict on balance change), fee configurations (evict on config update), user lookups, KYC tier info |
| 6.13 | Caching | **Cache eviction** | `@CacheEvict` on deposit/withdraw/transfer methods for wallet caches; on fee config updates for fee caches; on KYC tier change for tier cache |
| 6.14 | Config | **Email config** | `spring.mail.*` in `application.yml` ‚Äî SMTP host/port/credentials (dev: use Mailtrap or console output) |
| 6.15 | Test | **Scheduler idempotency tests** | Run cleanup twice, verify same result |
| 6.16 | Test | **Notification retry tests** | Mock failure, verify 3 retries, then maxed out |

**Deliverable**: Email/SMS alerts on transactions and KYC events. Daily cleanup jobs. Balance/fees/tiers cached with proper eviction.

