## Phase 9 ‚Äî Docker, CI/CD & Production Readiness
**Goal**: Containerized deployment, automated pipeline, production profiles.

| Step | Domain | Task | Details |
|------|--------|------|---------|
| 9.1 | Infra | **Dockerfile** | Multi-stage build: Maven compile ‚Üí JRE 17 runtime. Expose port 8080. Healthcheck via `/actuator/health` |
| 9.2 | Infra | **docker-compose.yml** | `api` service + `postgres` 16 service + `minio` (S3-compatible for KYC docs in dev) + optional `mailpit` (dev email) |
| 9.3 | Config | **application-prod.yml** | PostgreSQL connection (env vars), Flyway validate mode, CORS origin whitelist, Flutterwave API keys, KYC provider API keys, AWS S3 config (encryption), Redis config, secure cookie config |
| 9.4 | CI | **GitHub Actions workflow** | `.github/workflows/ci.yml` ‚Äî build, run tests (including integration), package JAR, build Docker image, push to registry (optional) |
| 9.5 | CI | **Pre-commit checks** | Optional `.husky` or GitHub Action for compile + test on push to any branch |
| 9.6 | Config | **Logging production config** | `logback-spring.xml` ‚Äî JSON format for production, rolling file appender, console for dev, masking of passwords/PINs/KYC data in logs |
| 9.7 | Config | **CORS configuration** | Allow specific origins (configurable), not `*` for production |
| 9.8 | Config | **Secrets management** | Flutterwave secret key, KYC provider API keys, S3 credentials, database password ‚Äî all from environment variables / secrets manager |
| 9.9 | Docs | **README.md** | Project overview, setup instructions (local dev), environment variables, API docs link, Docker instructions |
| 9.10 | Docs | **API curl examples** | Document key flows: register ‚Üí KYC Tier 2 ‚Üí deposit ‚Üí transfer ‚Üí withdraw ‚Üí issue virtual card |

**Deliverable**: `docker-compose up` runs the full stack with PostgreSQL, MinIO (KYC docs), and app. CI pipeline builds and tests.

