## Phase 12 ‚Äî Virtual Card Issuing ‚¨ÖÔ∏è NEW
**Goal**: Issue, fund, freeze, unfreeze, and close virtual debit cards backed by Flutterwave Issuing API or alternative provider.

| Step | Domain | Task | Details |
|------|--------|------|---------|
| 12.1 | Entity | **VirtualCard entity** | `id (UUID)`, `userId`, `providerCardId`, `panSuffix` (last 4 digits only), `currency` (USD default), `balance` (BigDecimal), `status` (INACTIVE/ACTIVE/FROZEN/CLOSED), `cardType` (SINGLE_USE/MULTI_USE), `issuedAt`, `expiresAt`, `dailyLimit`, `monthlyLimit`, `lastFundingAt`, `createdAt`, `updatedAt` |
| 12.2 | Migration | **Flyway V15** | `V15__create_virtual_cards_table.sql` |
| 12.3 | DTO | **Card DTOs** | `IssueCardRequest`, `CardResponse` (masked PAN: `**** **** **** 1234`, expiry, CVV masked), `FundCardRequest`, `CardTransactionResponse`, `CardStatusUpdateRequest` |
| 12.4 | Service | **CardService** | `issueCard(userId, cardType, currency)` ‚Äî verify KYC Tier 2+, check no duplicate active cards of same type, call issuing provider, store panSuffix only, return masked card details; `fundCard(cardId, amount, pin)` ‚Äî verify PIN, deduct from ZMW wallet at exchange rate, credit card balance, call provider to load funds; `freezeCard(cardId)`, `unfreezeCard(cardId)`, `closeCard(cardId)` ‚Äî update status locally + notify provider |
| 12.5 | Service | **CardProviderClient** | Interface for card issuing: `createCard(user, type, currency)`, `fundCard(providerCardId, amount, currency)`, `freezeCard(providerCardId)`, `unfreezeCard(providerCardId)`, `closeCard(providerCardId)`, `getCardTransactions(providerCardId)`. Primary impl: `FlutterwaveIssuingClient` |
| 12.6 | Service | **ExchangeRateService** | `convert(amount, fromCurrency, toCurrency)` ‚Äî fetch rate from Flutterwave or configurable provider, apply small spread (configurable), cache rates for 5 min. Used when funding USD cards from ZMW wallet |
| 12.7 | Controller | **CardController** | `POST /api/v1/cards` (issue), `GET /api/v1/cards` (list user's cards), `GET /api/v1/cards/{id}` (single card details, PAN masked), `POST /api/v1/cards/{id}/fund` (fund from wallet), `PATCH /api/v1/cards/{id}/status` (freeze/unfreeze), `DELETE /api/v1/cards/{id}` (close), `GET /api/v1/cards/{id}/transactions` (card spending history) |
| 12.8 | Controller | **Admin card controller** | `GET /api/v1/admin/cards` (all cards, filterable by status/user), `PATCH /api/v1/admin/cards/{id}/freeze`, `PATCH /api/v1/admin/cards/{id}/close` |
| 12.9 | Security | **Card access control** | Users see only their own cards. CVV view requires PIN re-verification (`POST /api/v1/cards/{id}/cvv` with PIN in body). PAN never returned in full ‚Äî only last 4 digits |
| 12.10 | Validation | **Card limits** | Max cards per user: 3. Single-use card auto-closes after first transaction. Multi-use card daily limit defaults to ZMW 5,000 equivalent (configurable per KYC tier) |
| 12.11 | Enhancement | **Spending notifications** | On card transaction (via provider webhook or polling), notify user via email/SMS |
| 12.12 | Enhancement | **Card expiry handling** | 30 days before expiry: send notification. On expiry: auto-close, return balance to wallet |
| 12.13 | Test | **CardService tests** | Issue (KYC check, duplicate prevention, provider call), fund (PIN verification, exchange rate, balance deduction), freeze/unfreeze/close lifecycle, balance return on close |
| 12.14 | Test | **Exchange rate tests** | Rate fetching, caching, spread application, stale rate handling |
| 12.15 | Integration | **Card lifecycle E2E** | Register ‚Üí KYC Tier 2 ‚Üí issue card ‚Üí fund card ‚Üí freeze ‚Üí unfreeze ‚Üí close ‚Üí balance returned |

**Deliverable**: Users can issue virtual USD cards, fund them from ZMW wallet, freeze/unfreeze, view masked details, and close with automatic balance return.

