## Entity Relationship Summary (Updated)

```
User (1) ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ (1) Wallet
User (1) ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ (N) RefreshToken
User (1) ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ (1) KycTier
User (1) ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ (N) KycDocument
User (1) ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ (N) VirtualCard
User (1) ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ (N) Notification
User (1) ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ (N) FlutterwaveTransaction
Wallet (1) ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ (N) Transaction (senderWallet)
Wallet (1) ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ (N) Transaction (receiverWallet)
Wallet (1) ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ (N) FlutterwaveTransaction
Transaction (1) ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ (1) FlutterwaveTransaction (localTransactionId)
Transaction (N) ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ (1) Transaction (relatedTransactionId) ‚Äî self-referencing for paired records
FeeConfiguration ‚Äî standalone, no FK
AuditLog ‚Äî standalone, entityType + entityId as polymorphic reference
IdempotencyKey ‚Äî standalone
NotificationAttempt (N) ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ (1) Notification
```

## Key Design Decisions

| Decision | Choice | Rationale |
|----------|--------|-----------|
| Wallet balance | Cached + DB-stored + ledger-verifiable | Balance is computed from transactions; stored balance used for fast reads; periodic reconciliation possible |
| Money precision | BigDecimal scale=2, HALF_EVEN | Banking standard, ngwee (ZMW cent) precision |
| Concurrency | `@Version` optimistic locking | Prevents lost updates on concurrent transfers |
| Audit writes | `@Async` + `CompletableFuture` | Non-blocking, won't slow financial operations |
| Token storage | BCrypt hash in DB (refresh tokens) | Server-side storage prevents MitM token theft persistence |
| Rate limiting | Token-bucket filter | Constant memory, burst-tolerant, O(1) per check |
| Migration strategy | Flyway, sequential versioned SQL | Explicit schema control, no auto-DDL in production |
| KYC provider | Abstract `KycProviderClient` interface | Swap SmileID / Dojah / IdentityPass without code changes |
| Payment gateway | Abstract `PaymentProvider` interface | Add Paystack, Stripe as additional providers later |
| KYC documents | S3/MinIO object storage, not DB BLOBs | Cheaper storage, CDN delivery, easier encryption, no DB bloat |
| Virtual card PAN | Never stored in full (last 4 digits only) | PCI-DSS scope reduction ‚Äî PAN not in application DB |
| Flutterwave webhook dedup | `flwRef` unique index + idempotency check | Prevents double-credit on webhook replay |
| Fee absorption | Configurable USER_PAYS / PLATFORM_PAYS | Business decision, not hardcoded |
| Exchange rate | 5-min cache with configurable spread | Avoids hitting Flutterwave rate API on every call |

